race.comment: HOUDINI (4) ran an encouraging race first up at Geelong, getting back and finding the line well to be beaten 2.5 lengths over 1512m. He put up some good numbers last time in and looks capable of getting to that level second up. LIM'S SMYTHE (1) was well backed and broke through for a smart victory at Sale when last seen, coming clear to score by a length as favourite. Bit more depth now but he can go on with the job. FIGLIO D'ARGENTO (2) has been close up without winning this time in, good in a stronger race at Flemington last time out. He can roll forward and take plenty of catching. COLOUR OUR WORLD (5) steps up past a mile for the first time. She stuck on well at Geelong last time out, ahead of HOUDINI, and should be in this for a long way. EN FLIQUE (7) dominated an easier race last time and has to be respected off that.
